message.content: One of the most significant events that happened in Italy in the past 5 years was the COVID-19 pandemic. Italy was one of the first countries in Europe to be severely affected by the virus, experiencing a high number of cases and fatalities. The government implemented strict lockdown measures to contain the spread, which had a significant impact on the country's economy and daily life. The pandemic had far-reaching consequences for Italy's healthcare system, tourism industry, and society as a whole.
